// MCP Server Setup
// Shared MCP server configuration used by both stdio and HTTP transports.
// Registers all MCP tools and their handlers, proxying most operations to the HTTP API server.

All tool handlers follow the same pattern: validate params, call the HTTP API, return JSON result.
Most tools require project + session params (session can be resolved from a todoId).
The API server base URL is derived from HOST/PORT environment variables (default: localhost:3737).

FUNCTION setupMCPServer() -> Server                                      EXPORT
  CALLS: dismissUI (tools/dismiss-ui), updateUI (tools/update-ui), renderUI (tools/render-ui),
         completeSkill (workflow/complete-skill), getKodexManager (services/kodex-manager),
         handleListProjects (tools/projects), handleCreateDesign (tools/design),
         updateTaskStatus (workflow/task-status), sessionRegistry (services/session-registry)
  Create a new MCP Server with tools and resources capabilities.
  Register resource handlers (currently empty — no resources exposed).
  Register all tool schemas via ListToolsRequestSchema.
  Register the tool dispatch handler via CallToolRequestSchema.

  Tool categories registered:

  Session management:
    generate_session_name, list_sessions, archive_session,
    get_session_state, update_session_state

  Project management:
    list_projects, register_project, unregister_project

  Diagrams:
    list_diagrams, get_diagram, create_diagram, update_diagram, patch_diagram,
    validate_diagram, preview_diagram, transpile_diagram, diagram_from_code,
    get_diagram_history, revert_diagram, export_diagram_png, export_diagram_svg

  Documents:
    list_documents, get_document, create_document, update_document, patch_document,
    preview_document, get_document_history, revert_document, delete_document,
    get_design_item, patch_design_item, describe_design_changes

  Designs (visual editor):
    create_design, update_design, get_design, list_designs, delete_design, export_design,
    add_design_node, update_design_node, remove_design_node, get_design_node,
    list_design_nodes, batch_design_operations, group/ungroup/reorder/duplicate/align/
    transform_design_nodes, create_design_from_tree, add_design_image, set_node_image,
    export_design_svg, export_design_code, export_design_png, lint_design, revert_design,
    get_design_history, describe_design, design_to_diagram, apply_design_tokens,
    create_design_tokens

  Annotations:
    get_annotations, annotate_node, remove_annotation

  Spreadsheets:
    create_spreadsheet, get_spreadsheet, update_spreadsheet, patch_spreadsheet,
    list_spreadsheets, delete_spreadsheet, get_spreadsheet_history, revert_spreadsheet,
    export_spreadsheet_csv

  Snippets:
    create_snippet, get_snippet, update_snippet, patch_snippet, list_snippets,
    delete_snippet, apply_snippet, export_snippet, snippet_history, revert_snippet

  Components:
    save_component, load_component, list_components, list_library_components,
    create_component, create_instance, detach_instance

  UI tools:
    render_ui, get_ui_response, update_ui, dismiss_ui

  Workflow:
    complete_skill, update_task_status, update_tasks_status, get_task_graph

  Terminal sessions:
    terminal_create_session, terminal_kill_session, terminal_list_sessions,
    terminal_rename_session, terminal_reorder_sessions

  Kodex (knowledge base):
    kodex_dashboard, kodex_list_topics, kodex_query_topic, kodex_create_topic,
    kodex_direct_create_topic, kodex_update_topic, kodex_direct_update_topic,
    kodex_flag_topic, kodex_list_flags, kodex_list_drafts, kodex_approve_draft,
    kodex_reject_draft, kodex_verify_topic, kodex_add_alias, kodex_remove_alias

  Todos:
    list_todos, list_todo_items, add_todo, remove_todo, update_todo

  Lessons:
    add_lesson, list_lessons

  Templates and misc:
    create_from_template, check_server_health, get_install_path,
    validate_session_links, add_design_snippet

---

FUNCTION generateSessionName() -> string
  Return a random "adjective-adjective-noun" name.

---

FUNCTION buildUrl(path, project, session, extraParams?) -> string
  Construct a full API URL with project/session query params.

---

FUNCTION extractDesignItem(content, itemNumber) -> item details
  Parse a design document to extract a specific "### Item N:" section.
  Return the item text, position indices, and total item count.
